Victoria police have revealed their romantic side in their search for the owner of a lost wedding ring.

The silver wedding band, inscribed with the words 'I love Julie' and a date in 2005, was found on a nature strip in Glen Waverly, south-east of Melbourne.

Officers have made it their mission to find the love-struck ring owner after the jewellery piece was handed in to them by a member of the public last week.

